name: F1
summary: Formula One (F1) has announced several changes to its calendar, with a focus on rationalizing the schedule for 2026. The Canadian Grand Prix (GP) will be shifted to May to accommodate the addition of other races. Additionally, Andretti is reportedly in discussions to join the F1 grid as a General Motors team. The calendar shake-up is expected to have a "significant" impact, and the 2026 season will also feature a new F1 Academy series with a 2025 calendar. Ferrari team principal Frederic Vasseur has outlined plans for Lewis Hamilton's arrival at the team, while Lando Norris has admitted he was not yet ready for an F1 title battle. F1 Fantasy experts are offering their top picks and predictions for the inaugural Las Vegas GP in 2024.

name: Daniel Jones
summary: Daniel Jones has been released by the New York Giants after being benched in favor of Tyrod Taylor. The move impacts the team's salary cap, with a $23 million injury guarantee being sidestepped. Jones reportedly addressed the QB change, while experts believe the move also reflects on the performance of head coach Brian Daboll and general manager Joe Schoen. Speculation has surfaced regarding Jones' potential landing spots, including the Broncos, Rams, and Panthers. Sources suggest that the relationship between Jones and the Giants had become strained before his benching. The departure of Jones marks the end of an era for the Giants and raises questions about the team's future direction.

name: Man on the Inside
summary: "A Man on the Inside," starring Ted Danson, has received critical acclaim from various outlets. Forbes labeled it one of the best Netflix shows of 2024, highlighting Danson's exceptional performance. Despite the praise, USA Today's review noted that the show's premise lost its way. Netflix Tudum provided an explanation of the show's ending, and MarieClaire.com covered details about a potential second season. The Los Angeles Times praised the show's balance of sweetness, seriousness, and humor. The Hollywood Reporter highlighted Danson's ability to evoke both laughter and tears. Roger Ebert called the show "lovely" and "moving." Variety described it as a "brilliant mystery comedy." The Guardian raved about Danson's comedic performance, calling the show "unbelievably sweet." MSNBC interviewed Danson about the show's inspiring message.

name: Surry Hills
summary: A fatal shooting occurred in Sydney's Surry Hills, with police launching a massive operation to locate the perpetrator. The victim, a man, was shot on a busy street and pronounced dead at the scene. Witnesses reported seeing a man fleeing the area in a dark-colored sedan. The same vehicle was later found alight in a nearby suburb. Authorities believe the incident is linked to an ongoing underworld dispute, with investigations ongoing to identify the suspects. The shooting has prompted a grim theory regarding potential motives, but details remain under wraps for now.
